
## 📌 Project Report: n8n Excel Automation Workflow

### 🔹 Overview

This project implements an end-to-end automation workflow using **n8n** to collect data via webhook, process it, update an Excel file, and store the updated file on **Google Drive**.

---

### 🔹 Workflow Summary

#### 1️⃣ Workflow Trigger & Webhook

* Workflow can be triggered using both **Manual Trigger** and **Webhook**.
* Webhook configured with **HTTP GET method** and no authentication.
* Verified successful execution through test webhook URL.

#### 2️⃣ Google Drive Access & Excel Download

* Connected Google Drive account in n8n.
* Downloaded an Excel (.xlsx) file using **File ID**.
* Ensured the file is received correctly in binary format.

#### 3️⃣ Excel Sheet Read

* Used **Spreadsheet File (Read)** node to extract Excel data.
* Configured with correct binary property (`data`) and XLSX format.
* Successfully converted Excel rows into structured JSON.

#### 4️⃣ Data Preparation

* Used **Edit Fields (Set)** node to prepare input fields:

  * First Name
  * Last Name
  * Email
  * Phone Number
* Mapped incoming data from webhook or manual input.

#### 5️⃣ Excel File Update

* Appended new records using **Spreadsheet File (Write)** node.
* Verified that new rows are added correctly to the Excel file.

#### 6️⃣ Upload Updated Excel to Google Drive

* Uploaded the updated Excel file back to Google Drive.
* Confirmed successful storage with latest data.

---

### 🔹 Outcome

* Fully automated workflow from data input to Excel update.
* Supports dynamic data via webhook.
* Eliminates manual Excel handling and ensures data consistency.

---

### 🔹 Tech Stack

* **n8n**
* **Google Drive API**
* **Excel (.xlsx)**
* **Webhook (HTTP GET)**

----



## 🔄 Workflow (End-to-End Automation)

```
Manual Trigger / Webhook
        ↓
Google Drive (Download Excel File)
        ↓
Spreadsheet File (Read Excel)
        ↓
Edit Fields (Prepare User Data)
        ↓
Spreadsheet File (Write / Append Row)
        ↓
Google Drive (Upload Updated Excel)
```

---

### 🧩 Workflow Explanation (Short)

* **Trigger:** Workflow can be started manually or via webhook request.
* **Download:** Excel file is fetched from Google Drive using File ID.
* **Read:** Existing Excel data is read and converted into JSON.
* **Prepare Data:** Incoming user details (First Name, Last Name, Email, Phone) are structured using Edit Fields.
* **Update Excel:** New data is appended as a new row in the Excel file.
* **Upload:** Updated Excel file is uploaded back to Google Drive.

---

### ✅ Key Features

* Supports **manual & webhook-based execution**
* Dynamic data handling
* Automated Excel update
* Cloud-based storage on Google Drive
* Beginner-friendly and scalable workflow

